# D.U.C.K – XR Dynamic User Context Kit

## Project
- **Name:** D.U.C.K (XR Dynamic User Context Kit).
- **Goal:** MR system on Meta Quest 3 that visualizes real-time biomarker-related signals (live heart rate from a watch, posture from a wearable, facial expression via MorphCast + Quest cameras, optional future modalities) to study how that affects behavior. End goal: NeuroSwarm (biodata + social interaction analysis). **Voice/microphone emotion is out of scope.**

## Authority docs
**`docs/FinalStretchDoc.md` is the prioritized specification** for scope, hardware, and goals. **`docs/MLOptions.md`** expands ML design (dual-model path, labels); if anything conflicts, **prefer `FinalStretchDoc.md`**. Other files under `docs/` are optional background or archive; do not use them to override `FinalStretchDoc.md` unless migrating content on purpose.

## Tech stack
- **MR app:** Unity, C#, Meta SDK / OpenXR, Meta Quest 3 — **display only** for ML; no on-headset inference for now.
- **Watch:** Live heart-rate streaming only (no sweat/EDA/SpO₂ from the watch in current plan); bridge TBD.
- **Posture sensor:** ESP32 + ADXL335 + vibration motor; C++ (Arduino/ESP32 toolchain); code in `arduino/`.
- **Facial expression:** [MorphCast](https://www.morphcast.com/) with Quest 3 cameras (features consumed on PC).
- **ML:** Dual path on **host PC**: **Random Forest** (fast, discrete labels) + **interval model** (richer situational analysis; algorithm TBD). See `docs/FinalStretchDoc.md` and `docs/MLOptions.md`. Continuous arousal/stress scores possible later, not committed.
- **Data flow:** Sensors / camera path → **host PC (all inference)** → Quest 3 **display only**.

## Conventions
- New Unity/MR code in the Unity project (e.g. `D.U.C.K-Unity/` or as specified).
- Arduino firmware and posture-sensor scripts in `arduino/`.
- Keep UI minimal and non-overwhelming; “put on head and it works” for MVP.
